1
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:33,520
If Elizabeth is listening right now,
Mary Katherine, what would you say to her?

2
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:38,800
That I miss her and I want her to know
that our whole family loves her.

3
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:43,800
I wonder why would somebody
want to kidnap Elizabeth?

4
00:00:47,440 --> 00:00:49,840
I was nine years old
when Elizabeth was taken.

5
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:54,440
I missed not having my sister.

6
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:56,920
She was my best friend.

7
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:06,280
I think you're asking me
have I dealt with it?

8
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:08,880
I think it's something I still deal with.

9
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:22,160
That night, Elizabeth and I
said our prayers together

10
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:23,520
and we went to sleep.

11
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:30,800
The next thing I remember,

12
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:34,120
there was a man in my bedroom

13
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:40,680
telling Elizabeth if she screamed,
he would kill her.

14
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:45,520
I was paralyzed.

15
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:48,880
I just couldn't believe what's happening.

16
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:59,760
I finally worked up enough courage
to tell my parents Elizabeth was gone,

17
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:02,800
that a man had come in and taken her.

18
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:07,040
<i>Every parent's worst nightmare.</i>

19
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,680
<i>A 14-year-old Utah girl</i>

20
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:11,520
<i>taken from her bedroom
while her family was sleeping.</i>

21
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,920
<i>How could it happen
right in her own bedroom</i>

22
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,560
<i>in an affluent community?</i>

23
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:19,000
<i>Where in the world is Elizabeth Smart?</i>

24
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:23,680
This case captivated the nation.

25
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:26,320
<i>Authorities have launched
a nationwide manhunt.</i>

26
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:29,160
It just had all the elements
of a Hollywood story.

27
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:31,680
<i>A strange and puzzling new twist tonight.</i>

28
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:36,000
<i>Police are continuing
to focus on her family members.</i>

29
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:39,240
Law enforcement don't believe
we're telling the truth.

30
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:43,600
As a family, we weren't gonna
just leave it to the authorities.

31
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:46,640
There is somebody out there
that knows something.

32
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:54,040
I had this overwhelming feeling
Elizabeth was still out there.

33
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,600
I needed to find my daughter.

34
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:06,680
When I made my bid for freedom,
I wanted it to be a sure thing.

35
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,360
I was gonna do whatever it took

36
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:11,640
to escape.

37
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:32,800
As a father,
you are there to protect your child

38
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,440
and to keep them from harm's way.

39
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:40,400
That didn't happen.
I didn't keep her from harm's way.

40
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:47,120
That just repeats over in your mind,
over and over and over again.

41
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:53,600
I remember specifically at 3:58,

42
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:58,800
Mary Katherine came into the room
saying that somebody had taken Elizabeth.

43
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:01,640
I thought, "You know,
you've just had a bad nightmare."

44
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:04,440
"Elizabeth is probably
somewhere in the house."

45
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:10,280
But as we went room to room,
the anxiety started rising.

46
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:17,800
In the kitchen, I saw this cut screen.

47
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:20,920
And the window was wide open.

48
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:25,400
My wife screamed, "Call 911!"

49
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:33,640
On June 5th, early in the morning,
my pager was going off.

50
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:36,480
We had had a kidnapping of a young woman

51
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:37,880
up in Federal Heights.

52
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:42,000
The abduction of a child
taken from their bedroom

53
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:44,240
is extremely rare.

54
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:47,160
So I felt some pretty good urgency
to get down there.

55
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:55,360
I went up to the scene.
A captain briefed me.

56
00:04:57,560 --> 00:05:00,320
Elizabeth Smart was
a young 14-year-old girl

57
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,080
involved in music,

58
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,960
involved heavily with her church.

59
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:08,720
The family said
she'd been taken from her bedroom

60
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,200
in the middle of the night.

61
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,000
The window was open.

62
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,880
There was a cut screen.

63
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:18,120
Then outside,

64
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:20,440
somebody had put a chair up
against the wall.

65
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:25,640
My initial impression was this isn't
gonna be a long-term, ongoing thing.

66
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:28,320
We'll have answers in 48 hours.

67
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,360
I was wrong.

68
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:35,200
This morning at about two o'clock,
we had what appears to be an abduction

69
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:37,800
from a home up here
in the Federal Heights area.

70
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:40,400
Terror set in as the news spread.

71
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:45,320
In Salt Lake City,
I'm Nicea DeGering, 7 News at 11.

72
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,720
I recall my first report on the story.

73
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:51,440
"A little girl is missing
in Federal Heights,

74
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:54,600
taken from her bedroom
in the middle of the night."

75
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:59,880
And I remember being shocked by the words
as they came out of my mouth.

76
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:06,640
Federal Heights is one of
the most ritzy areas in Salt Lake City.

77
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,600
The homes are gorgeous.

78
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:13,560
The Mormon church is interwoven
into the community.

79
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:16,280
You wouldn't think crime happens here.

80
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:21,160
And I remember thinking,
"Is this a real kidnapping?"

81
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:30,440
I got a call, and my brother Ed said,
"Please come, I need your help."

82
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:34,280
I remember walking into the front door.

83
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:36,800
Ed came over and got me.

84
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:39,800
And he just looked like
he'd been put through a meat grinder.

85
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:41,960
Elizabeth, if you're out there,

86
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:45,720
we're doing everything we possibly can
to help you.

87
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,680
We love you.

88
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,720
We want you to come home safely to us.

89
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:56,560
Elizabeth's mother, Lois,

90
00:06:58,440 --> 00:07:02,480
was in the front room
surrounded by family and friends.

91
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:06,800
And there was just this blood-curdling

92
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:11,000
moan and cry coming from her.

93
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,000
"Where is my daughter?"

94
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:23,880
Right from the get-go,
we set up a phone room to take tips.

95
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:27,920
The number of leads that came in
from the public numbered about 40,000.

96
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:32,080
And so we assembled a team
of hundreds of investigators.

97
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:35,080
Oh well, no matter how much lipstick
you put on this pig,

98
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,400
I'm not gonna look any better.

99
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:41,720
We went out to the school
and to contact Elizabeth's friends.

100
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:50,720
Our investigation revealed no boyfriends,
no shady associations, no drug use.

101
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:55,960
Elizabeth Smart was just a very typical
14-year-old devout Mormon girl

102
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:58,440
living a very normal life
in a very nice neighborhood.

103
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:03,880
Everyone knew who Elizabeth was
up in that area.

104
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:07,560
And by 4:30,
the neighborhood had mobilized.

105
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:12,960
Any of you know CPR or rock climbing?

106
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:15,560
Our community is very strong,

107
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:20,600
and so everybody was willing to just
drop what they were doing and search.

108
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:22,040
Why are you doing this?

109
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:27,120
I love Ed and Lois,
and they are a wonderful family.

110
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:29,520
My handsome husband.

111
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:32,840
Our home is nestled up into the hills.

112
00:08:32,920 --> 00:08:35,000
Oh, happiness and joy.

113
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:39,920
Lois and I and the family
had been there for about eight years.

114
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:44,360
We had six children. Four boys, two girls.

115
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:45,960
Hi, Mom.

116
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,680
Hi, Elizabeth.

117
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:51,800
Elizabeth, you know,
she was the first daughter.

118
00:08:57,120 --> 00:09:01,840
She was fiercely competitive,
especially with her brothers.

119
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:08,680
As far as, you know, her inner strength,
she just really had a very strong spirit.

120
00:09:11,680 --> 00:09:14,240
<i>Authorities have launched
a nationwide manhunt today,</i>

121
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,320
<i>Thursday, June the 6th.</i>

122
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:19,280
<i>The search goes on
this morning for kidnapped Utah teenager</i>

123
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,640
<i>Elizabeth Smart.</i>

124
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:22,160
An innocent girl has been stolen

125
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:24,440
from what should've been
the safest place in the world.

126
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:27,360
Today, Salt Lake City police
announced a reward.

127
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:30,560
A quarter of a million dollars
for Elizabeth's safe return.

128
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,840
The media response to this case
was insane.

129
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:33,920
<i>CBS News.</i>

130
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:36,240
<i>- Fox News.
- NBC News.</i>

131
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:38,360
There was a lot of pressure
on the police department

132
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,640
to try and resolve the case
very, very quickly.

133
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:44,040
There was so little evidence to go on.

134
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:46,920
But there was a witness to the kidnapping…

135
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:52,880
The nine-year-old sister
of Elizabeth Smart, Mary Katherine.

136
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,000
As a nine-year-old,
I don't think I understood

137
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:04,160
what was going on.

138
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:10,680
Just that my sister was gone
and I was very frightened.

139
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:14,480
We tried to do everything together.

140
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:17,880
I wanted to be just like her.

141
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:22,280
We did fight, mostly over how messy I was.

142
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:28,160
But any opportunity to be able
to spend time with her, I was there.

143
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:40,600
Mary Katherine was very likely
going to be the key to finding Elizabeth.

144
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:45,040
Anybody who has a traumatic memory
will make certain memory imprints.

145
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:50,360
And so we wanted her interviewed
in a controlled, safe environment.

146
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:55,760
The guy said, "Be quiet."

147
00:10:55,840 --> 00:11:02,040
"If you scream, I'll shoot you.
But if you don't, I won't harm you."

148
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:05,560
Did his voice sound familiar to you?

149
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,200
Yeah.

150
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:11,480
Can you tell me
where you've heard that before?

151
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:15,520
No, I can't remember.

152
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:20,520
Mary Katherine had indicated
that the voice seemed familiar to her.

153
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:24,320
She couldn't say whose voice it was,
but it was a familiar voice.

154
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:29,000
You know, first impression
looking at the Smarts,

155
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:33,000
they looked like a happy, normal family.

156
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:37,880
But, statistically, more often than not,

157
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:42,440
the perpetrator of this type of crime
is a parent or a family member.

158
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:46,520
So we started looking very hard at them.

159
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:52,560
We brought members of the Smart family in.

160
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,560
We did in-depth interviews.

161
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:59,480
And there were a couple things
that came up that made us go, "Huh."

162
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:05,200
I was told that the alarm
had been inadvertently left off.

163
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:09,080
And the window.

164
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:11,680
When I looked at it the first morning,

165
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:13,920
there were no scuff marks
on the outside wall.

166
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:18,360
Even if you step up on a chair,
you're gonna make a scuff mark.

167
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:20,080
I did not see any.

168
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:27,280
My initial assessment was
maybe this wasn't the point of entry.

169
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:29,920
Maybe it was a staged one.

170
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:36,560
Someone had cut the screen after the fact,
but didn't come and go through the window.

171
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:39,880
So we searched the home.

172
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:45,160
We're looking for any indication
that harm befell Elizabeth.

173
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:50,720
Is there even a body in the home?

174
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:54,760
We have a really good bloodhound
on the department.

175
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:57,360
His name is JJ.
We had a lot of confidence in him.

176
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:01,760
And he picked up the scent for Elizabeth.

177
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:05,640
Went out the back,
and then up into the trees.

178
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,640
And he followed a trail,

179
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:14,360
got up to the street up there,
which is a dead end,

180
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:17,480
and lost the scent.

181
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:24,600
I made the assumption

182
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:28,760
that she was probably
taken away in an automobile.

183
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:34,560
There's some indication
that this may have been an inside job.

184
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:37,960
Police confirming they have taken
12 computers from the family.

185
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:41,560
We were peppering police.

186
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:45,200
Is it the family?
Are we looking at the family?

187
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:52,840
I want to thank you all for your help.
I can't thank you enough.

188
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:57,640
I… I know it's gonna take
everyone's effort to find her.

189
00:13:57,720 --> 00:14:02,160
It's really hard to think of somebody
coming in there and taking her.

190
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:05,840
I… I would do anything
to have her back in my arms.

191
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:10,840
Ed and Lois Smart,
I think initially you felt their grief,

192
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,720
but it definitely shifted.

193
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:18,040
People would watch Ed on TV
when he was talking,

194
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:21,920
and they would make statements like,
"There are no tears when he's crying."

195
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:27,480
There was a sense of,
"Is he telling us everything?"

196
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,600
"Could he be involved?"

197
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,640
Something strange about that story.

198
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:39,320
As a reporter, you… you…
you ask some good questions,

199
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:41,480
but there are a lot more questions
to be asked.

200
00:14:41,560 --> 00:14:43,160
- Like?
- It doesn't ring true.

201
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:45,240
And it's somebody
that seems to have understood

202
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:47,880
the layout of the home
and how to find her in the home.

203
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:51,720
<i>They have given
the father of Elizabeth a polygraph test.</i>

204
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:02,120
Sometimes children are…
are killed by their own parents.

205
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:06,800
And there were theories
of what had happened.

206
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:11,280
One was that Ed had killed her
and disposed of her.

207
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:16,720
I had a call from Lois, my wife,

208
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:19,640
and I got down there,

209
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:23,240
and, um,

210
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:27,360
I saw this… this tear.

211
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:30,280
And she basically said,

212
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:33,440
"Law enforcement don't believe
that you're telling the truth,

213
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:35,240
that you're hiding something."

214
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:41,080
I was overwhelmed
to the point that I was shaking,

215
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:44,720
and I couldn't, um, stop shaking.

216
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:48,400
I had absolutely nothing to do with this.

217
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:52,200
And my father said,
"If you don't calm down,

218
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:53,800
I'm gonna commit you."

219
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:55,920
So he took me over to the hospital

220
00:15:57,000 --> 00:16:00,040
and put me in the psychiatric ward,
and I…

221
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:02,840
I cried that whole night.

222
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:11,600
To have your daughter go missing
is horrendous.

223
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:13,240
Do you like that, Elizabeth?

224
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:17,840
And then to be a possible suspect…

225
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:21,400
I was beyond words.

226
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:27,760
<i>In Utah, police searching
for 14-year-old Elizabeth Smart</i>

227
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:31,320
<i>are continuing to focus
on her family members.</i>

228
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:35,760
Scrutinize everybody.
Anything it takes. Do it. Do it.

229
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:38,760
Newsweek <i>magazine</i>
<i>was reporting that her father, Ed Smart,</i>

230
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:40,800
<i>that he completely cleared
a polygraph test,</i>

231
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:44,920
<i>but his brother Tom's polygraph,
that was inconclusive.</i>

232
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,840
I had… three brothers.

233
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:52,240
Tom was kind of
a little bit on the edge of things,

234
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,640
always getting into some trouble.

235
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:59,080
She plays the harp like an angel,
and she rides a horse like a cowboy.

236
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:02,800
She's… she's unbelievable.

237
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:05,560
Is a failed polygraph test suspicious?

238
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:07,920
Yes, absolutely.

239
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,200
Maybe one brother
doesn't like another brother.

240
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:12,440
Don't get me wrong on that.

241
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:14,200
- This family...
- We love each other.

242
00:17:14,280 --> 00:17:17,240
We love each other
more than any brothers possibly could.

243
00:17:17,320 --> 00:17:22,760
A couple of the camera people said,
