what the man looked like,

721
00:53:53,560 --> 00:53:56,520
and she was sketching
while we were talking.

722
00:53:57,720 --> 00:54:01,040
I was really hopeful that
in going out with that picture,

723
00:54:01,120 --> 00:54:03,360
we would find Emmanuel.

724
00:54:04,360 --> 00:54:09,880
The importance of getting the information
out to the public was huge.

725
00:54:12,200 --> 00:54:14,360
Yes, we're making progress.

726
00:54:15,280 --> 00:54:16,960
Let's find this individual.

727
00:54:18,240 --> 00:54:19,680
Law enforcement, "No."

728
00:54:21,840 --> 00:54:23,480
"You can't put this out there."

729
00:54:24,440 --> 00:54:27,600
Our perception was,
if we went public with it,

730
00:54:27,680 --> 00:54:30,600
we could scare the perpetrator away.

731
00:54:32,360 --> 00:54:36,440
But now we knew a name,
and we had a sketch of him.

732
00:54:37,120 --> 00:54:42,120
He was medium height,
thin build, dark hair, clean-shaven.

733
00:54:50,280 --> 00:54:53,600
Emmanuel and Hephzibah
got into a massive fight.

734
00:54:54,760 --> 00:54:58,680
She was angry that he would go down
into Salt Lake and he'd get all this food,

735
00:54:58,760 --> 00:55:03,160
and we were stuck up
hiding in the mountains, starving.

736
00:55:04,040 --> 00:55:09,480
So ultimately, it was decided
we would go down to Salt Lake.

737
00:55:12,560 --> 00:55:16,560
This was a chance to be recognized.
Maybe I'd get away.

738
00:55:22,520 --> 00:55:25,720
We started down, and I saw people.

739
00:55:27,240 --> 00:55:29,400
Was this gonna be a chance to be rescued?

740
00:55:31,160 --> 00:55:34,120
But if I was up in the mountains

741
00:55:34,200 --> 00:55:37,520
and I saw three people
that looked really strange

742
00:55:39,640 --> 00:55:42,600
I don't think I'd stop
and say hi to them either.

743
00:55:45,240 --> 00:55:49,120
The thought of crying out
did cross my mind.

744
00:55:49,960 --> 00:55:52,200
But I was 14.

745
00:55:52,280 --> 00:55:56,480
I had been extremely abused for months.

746
00:55:58,040 --> 00:56:02,920
When I disobeyed, I was raped.
I did have food withheld from me.

747
00:56:03,840 --> 00:56:09,320
So when I made my bid for freedom,
I wanted it to be a sure thing.

748
00:56:14,440 --> 00:56:18,000
We eventually made it down
from the mountains.

749
00:56:19,160 --> 00:56:21,520
I knew exactly where we were at.

750
00:56:21,600 --> 00:56:24,680
I was familiar with all the places
that were around.

751
00:56:25,800 --> 00:56:28,600
I knew exactly how long
it would take me to get home.

752
00:56:30,680 --> 00:56:32,720
I knew I could walk it. I could run it.

753
00:56:38,360 --> 00:56:41,880
But I had been so far away for so long.

754
00:56:45,360 --> 00:56:48,080
It was like seeing everything
through a different body.

755
00:56:50,240 --> 00:56:53,640
Like being in a parallel universe.

756
00:56:57,000 --> 00:57:00,720
I was walking through a place
that should be very, very safe,

757
00:57:04,080 --> 00:57:07,920
but now was fraught with peril.

758
00:57:12,600 --> 00:57:16,920
We went to the Salt Lake Library
to go and look at maps.

759
00:57:20,560 --> 00:57:24,760
And all of a sudden,
this man started approaching us.

760
00:57:26,840 --> 00:57:30,640
"I'm a homicide detective,
and I need to ask you a few questions."

761
00:57:33,000 --> 00:57:36,960
"I just need to make sure that this girl
is not this girl that we're looking for."

762
00:57:37,040 --> 00:57:38,120
"Can I see her face?"

763
00:57:41,360 --> 00:57:43,360
Emmanuel was like, "I'm sorry, but no."

764
00:57:43,440 --> 00:57:46,960
"Like, that would be against our faith.
That would be against our religion."

765
00:57:47,480 --> 00:57:50,040
"The only people
that will ever see her face

766
00:57:50,120 --> 00:57:52,400
are her future husband

767
00:57:52,480 --> 00:57:54,240
and myself, her father."

768
00:57:56,800 --> 00:57:58,800
I wanted to yell out.

769
00:57:59,920 --> 00:58:02,600
But Hephzibah grasped my leg.

770
00:58:11,120 --> 00:58:13,960
And finally, the detective…

771
00:58:16,000 --> 00:58:17,480
Was convinced.

772
00:58:20,480 --> 00:58:24,720
I didn't feel safe enough crying out.

773
00:58:24,800 --> 00:58:28,720
And that lifeline disappeared.

774
00:58:34,640 --> 00:58:38,400
After the confrontation
with the homicide detective,

775
00:58:38,480 --> 00:58:43,080
Emmanuel rushed to get me
back up into the mountains.

776
00:58:43,880 --> 00:58:48,720
He was… very anxious.

777
00:58:50,560 --> 00:58:55,280
And he made up his mind.
We needed to leave Salt Lake City.

778
00:58:59,720 --> 00:59:05,040
As we moved away from Salt Lake,
I thought of my little sister.

779
00:59:05,120 --> 00:59:09,040
What was she doing? Where was she at?
Was she still sleeping in our bed?

780
00:59:12,360 --> 00:59:14,920
I realized I might not ever
see my family again.

781
00:59:15,000 --> 00:59:19,320
I might not ever come back here again.
I might not ever…

782
00:59:20,680 --> 00:59:22,840
You know, I might not make it.

783
00:59:24,920 --> 00:59:27,040
I just wanted to tell them,

784
00:59:27,120 --> 00:59:31,080
"I'm still alive.
Don't stop looking for me."

785
00:59:37,040 --> 00:59:40,040
Both Mom and Dad
have been so wonderful to us.

786
00:59:41,160 --> 00:59:43,920
So understanding and so considerate.

787
00:59:44,520 --> 00:59:47,240
Christmas 2002,

788
00:59:47,320 --> 00:59:51,800
everyone's trying to put on a brave face.

789
00:59:52,440 --> 00:59:57,000
My mom tried her best to make things
as normal as possible for us.

790
00:59:57,480 --> 01:00:01,080
But I thought for sure, like,
we were never gonna see her again.

791
01:00:03,320 --> 01:00:07,120
<i>It has been almost six months
since 14-year-old Elizabeth Smart</i>

792
01:00:07,200 --> 01:00:10,080
<i>vanished from her home
in Salt Lake City, Utah.</i>

793
01:00:10,160 --> 01:00:15,600
I remember one day I was in the temple,
and I overheard somebody say,

794
01:00:16,920 --> 01:00:18,600
"Can you believe Ed Smart?"

795
01:00:19,280 --> 01:00:22,000
"You know,
he still thinks that she's alive."

796
01:00:22,080 --> 01:00:25,680
<i>The sense is this investigation
is stalling or has stalled?</i>

797
01:00:25,760 --> 01:00:29,520
<i>No. No. It has not stalled.
It is not stalling.</i>

798
01:00:32,200 --> 01:00:34,040
At the end of 2002,

799
01:00:34,120 --> 01:00:38,680
I was offered a position
as a chief of police up in Ketchum, Idaho.

800
01:00:42,120 --> 01:00:43,240
I talked to Ed and Lois,

801
01:00:43,320 --> 01:00:46,040
told them I hated to leave the case
in the middle of it.

802
01:00:48,040 --> 01:00:52,120
Up in Idaho, I would go home from work
and I would open up my computer

803
01:00:52,200 --> 01:00:55,520
and I would pore over these leads,

804
01:00:55,600 --> 01:01:00,240
and… and just hoping that I could find
something that we'd missed.

805
01:01:02,440 --> 01:01:04,240
I was obsessed.

806
01:01:05,120 --> 01:01:06,560
I was haunted by it.

807
01:01:06,640 --> 01:01:11,520
Afraid I might go to my grave
with this mystery haunting me.

808
01:01:15,080 --> 01:01:17,960
Thank goodness the family
were going to do whatever they could do

809
01:01:18,040 --> 01:01:19,440
to get Elizabeth back.

810
01:01:22,520 --> 01:01:24,040
<i>With Richard Ricci's death,</i>

811
01:01:24,120 --> 01:01:26,640
<i>the investigation
into Elizabeth Smart's kidnapping</i>

812
01:01:26,720 --> 01:01:28,320
<i>appears to be at a standstill.</i>

813
01:01:29,600 --> 01:01:33,200
The police had spent thousands
of man-hours trying to find Elizabeth,

814
01:01:33,280 --> 01:01:37,120
probably more than any single thing
in the history of Utah.

815
01:01:37,200 --> 01:01:40,080
And I think that they were done,
and they believed they had their man,

816
01:01:41,280 --> 01:01:42,600
Richard Ricci.

817
01:01:45,160 --> 01:01:49,440
All of us were wanting
to jump out of our seats and scream,

818
01:01:50,200 --> 01:01:51,880
"Well, what about Emmanuel?"

819
01:01:53,680 --> 01:01:58,040
Here we have the person
that was in the room,

820
01:01:58,120 --> 01:02:00,520
that said, "It's not Richard Ricci."

821
01:02:01,960 --> 01:02:03,280
"It's Emmanuel."

822
01:02:04,600 --> 01:02:06,880
We want to find this person.

823
01:02:08,680 --> 01:02:11,440
This is eight months, we've never
crossed the police on anything,

824
01:02:11,520 --> 01:02:15,280
even though many reasons
why we could have been mad.

825
01:02:16,240 --> 01:02:19,480
But we weren't gonna
just leave it to the authorities.

826
01:02:20,000 --> 01:02:21,640
This is the biggest lead we have.

827
01:02:21,720 --> 01:02:26,200
<i>Now we've got breaking news
on the Elizabeth Smart abduction case.</i>

828
01:02:26,280 --> 01:02:31,000
<i>I know in my heart, I absolutely know
that there is somebody out there</i>

829
01:02:31,080 --> 01:02:33,560
that knows something about this.

830
01:02:33,640 --> 01:02:35,600
And so we released the sketch.

831
01:02:36,560 --> 01:02:38,600
Of course that fired up interest.

832
01:02:41,240 --> 01:02:44,360
It just takes one person
knowing some information

833
01:02:44,440 --> 01:02:46,360
that will bring everything to an end.

834
01:02:48,480 --> 01:02:51,000
A few days after the press conference,

835
01:02:51,080 --> 01:02:55,560
I got a call from a man who said
he thought he might know who Emmanuel was.

836
01:02:55,640 --> 01:02:59,280
He had, uh, read it in the <i>Deseret News,</i>
he had seen the sketch.

837
01:02:59,800 --> 01:03:01,560
He said that chills went down his spine.

838
01:03:04,040 --> 01:03:08,280
And he thought there was a chance
that it could be his brother-in-law.

839
01:03:17,560 --> 01:03:19,920
<i>Personally,
I would be very, very surprised</i>

840
01:03:20,000 --> 01:03:22,040
<i>if he did have anything to do with it.</i>

841
01:03:22,120 --> 01:03:26,680
<i>But… he's just crazy enough, um,</i>

842
01:03:26,760 --> 01:03:30,160
<i>that there's a possibility.</i>

843
01:03:30,240 --> 01:03:32,600
<i>I do know that he does have a…</i>

844
01:03:32,680 --> 01:03:36,480
<i>Uh, a teepee
that he's had up in the mountains.</i>

845
01:03:38,080 --> 01:03:42,040
<i>But he has never ever
let any of the family know where.</i>

846
01:03:42,120 --> 01:03:43,160
<i>Right.</i>

847
01:03:43,240 --> 01:03:45,800
<i>If he really does have
something to do with it,</i>

848
01:03:45,880 --> 01:03:48,360
<i>there's a really good chance
that she's still alive.</i>

849
01:03:50,520 --> 01:03:51,960
Wow.

850
01:03:52,040 --> 01:03:53,160
Crazy.

851
01:03:54,320 --> 01:03:58,640
We thought, this is the main suspect,
and we've got to find this son of a bitch.

852
01:04:01,200 --> 01:04:05,120
Everything he said just fit like a glove.

853
01:04:05,200 --> 01:04:07,400
Tom had them send a picture over.

854
01:04:12,720 --> 01:04:15,280
That is Emmanuel.

855
01:04:15,360 --> 01:04:17,400
Brian David Mitchell.

856
01:04:25,320 --> 01:04:26,320
My phone rings.

857
01:04:27,440 --> 01:04:30,280
First thing I did is check
Brian David Mitchell on the computer

858
01:04:30,360 --> 01:04:32,440
and found out that, strangely enough,

859
01:04:32,520 --> 01:04:35,840
he'd been arrested for stealing beer
from the Albertsons store.

860
01:04:35,920 --> 01:04:39,560
And so, thankfully, they had taken
a Polaroid photograph of him

861
01:04:39,640 --> 01:04:41,760
during his shoplift arrest.

862
01:04:46,360 --> 01:04:51,520
He was dressed as some sort of
itinerant fundamentalist preacher.

863
01:04:54,000 --> 01:04:56,800
He had on a long robe,
and he had a long beard.

864
01:04:59,080 --> 01:05:02,560
And the striking thing
about the photograph is that

865
01:05:02,640 --> 01:05:05,640
his arrest was during the time period
Elizabeth had been kidnapped.

866
01:05:07,480 --> 01:05:10,440
So the police had him,
and they let him go.

867
01:05:12,440 --> 01:05:14,840
It was extremely frustrating.

868
01:05:16,560 --> 01:05:20,080
When I see this photo of him,
I realize, I know this guy.

869
01:05:20,160 --> 01:05:23,000
I've encountered him many times, begging.

870
01:05:23,560 --> 01:05:27,800
And he had a woman with him
who most of the time was holding a doll,

871
01:05:27,880 --> 01:05:29,880
and it… it was bizarre.

872
01:05:33,560 --> 01:05:37,840
So I put together a flyer
that we could distribute around town.

873
01:05:37,920 --> 01:05:42,200
Had three or four pictures of him,
"Wanted for questioning."

874
01:05:44,680 --> 01:05:47,360
All of a sudden,
the family was totally supercharged.

875
01:05:49,680 --> 01:05:52,360
It was full throttle
trying to find this guy.

876
01:05:54,760 --> 01:05:56,400
Leads started coming in,

877
01:05:56,480 --> 01:05:58,240
and we were able
to trace Brian's movements

878
01:05:58,320 --> 01:06:00,840
for the last, uh,
couple of years of his life.

879
01:06:03,920 --> 01:06:06,960
He was married to a woman
named Wanda Barzee.

880
01:06:09,560 --> 01:06:13,680
They had traveled extensively together
on foot around the United States,

881
01:06:14,200 --> 01:06:17,080
preaching the gospel
as they interpreted it.

882
01:06:20,200 --> 01:06:22,880
He believed himself to be
a prophet of God.

883
01:06:23,440 --> 01:06:28,280
In the last few years, he seemed to be
spinning into a violent state of mind.

884
01:06:30,400 --> 01:06:33,560
Brian Mitchell's ex-wife called.

885
01:06:34,720 --> 01:06:38,920
And for two hours, we sat there
and talked about Brian.

886
01:06:41,600 --> 01:06:44,120
We found out he's a dangerous individual.

887
01:06:46,880 --> 01:06:49,000
She had this fear of mice,

888
01:06:49,080 --> 01:06:51,840
and so he killed a bunch of mice
and put them in the stove

889
01:06:51,920 --> 01:06:54,480
so when she opened the stove,
there were all these dead mice.

890
01:06:56,000 --> 01:07:00,280
And there were historical allegations
of him sexually abusing children.

891
01:07:04,960 --> 01:07:08,320
It was heartbreaking to think
what Elizabeth could be going through.

892
01:07:09,600 --> 01:07:12,240
We had one purpose and one purpose only,

893
01:07:12,320 --> 01:07:15,080
to find Elizabeth
and bring Elizabeth back.

894
01:07:18,680 --> 01:07:22,240
We were going after him.
No mercy at this point.

895
01:07:22,320 --> 01:07:23,880
We're gonna find this guy.

896
01:07:24,840 --> 01:07:27,320
We started passing these flyers around,

897
01:07:27,400 --> 01:07:33,000
and one of my daughters said her friends
had seen these rogue people with veils

898
01:07:33,080 --> 01:07:35,280
at a place called Souper Salad.

899
01:07:37,280 --> 01:07:40,760
And so we went there,
and we talked to one of the waitresses.

900
01:07:42,240 --> 01:07:45,560
"We think that this might be
the person that took Elizabeth."

901
01:07:45,640 --> 01:07:47,920
And she said,
"Oh yeah, the… the Jesus people."

902
01:07:48,000 --> 01:07:51,320
"They would come in,
and there were three of them."

903
01:07:54,560 --> 01:07:56,320
"And one of them was a girl."

904
01:07:58,480 --> 01:07:59,840
They kept her veiled,

905
01:08:00,760 --> 01:08:03,840
but, I mean, obviously to eat,
the veil had to come down some.

906
01:08:05,280 --> 01:08:06,720
And she said, "Tom,

907
01:08:08,200 --> 01:08:09,680
I think that was Elizabeth."

908
01:08:10,760 --> 01:08:12,160
And, um,

909
01:08:13,000 --> 01:08:15,400
it felt like I was struck.

910
01:08:16,480 --> 01:08:20,080
I fell to my knees.
I said, "My God, she's alive."

911
01:08:28,120 --> 01:08:31,040
The public is the greatest resource.

912
01:08:33,640 --> 01:08:36,920
We had a number of people
that sighted him.

913
01:08:40,000 --> 01:08:42,080
We found a party that they had been at.

914
01:08:44,640 --> 01:08:46,520
It gives me chills to think,

915
01:08:47,240 --> 01:08:49,840
but you never expected a kidnapping.

916
01:08:51,320 --> 01:08:54,560
I felt pretty much like an idiot.

917
01:08:54,640 --> 01:08:56,480
I felt blind.

918
01:08:59,160 --> 01:09:01,440
The light was getting closer and closer.

919
01:09:03,640 --> 01:09:05,760
She's out there, and she's still alive.

920
01:09:09,240 --> 01:09:13,640
But there hadn't been any verifiable
reports of him since October.

921
01:09:31,840 --> 01:09:36,240
They had decided
on a little place outside of San Diego

922
01:09:36,320 --> 01:09:37,840
called Lakeside.

923
01:09:39,040 --> 01:09:43,200
And I'd been kept at this camp
for quite a while.

924
01:09:50,360 --> 01:09:52,240
Being raped was horrific.

925
01:09:53,600 --> 01:09:57,640
But sometimes I also had to wonder
if maybe listening to him wasn't worse.

926
01:10:00,920 --> 01:10:04,520
He talked nonstop
about how special he was,

927
01:10:04,600 --> 01:10:08,040
about how difficult these things that…

928
01:10:08,120 --> 01:10:11,320
That in any other circumstance
would be wrong to do,

929
01:10:11,400 --> 01:10:13,240
and he didn't want to do it,

930
01:10:13,320 --> 01:10:15,960
but he had to
because God commanded him to.

931
01:10:19,280 --> 01:10:23,280
One night he started to talk about
the places that they were going to go to,

932
01:10:23,360 --> 01:10:27,800
cities like New York, Boston,
far away from the West.

933
01:10:27,880 --> 01:10:31,960
And, I mean, I just remember sitting there
listening to them talk about it

934
01:10:32,040 --> 01:10:36,480
and thinking,
if we go to any other big city,

935
01:10:37,160 --> 01:10:39,360
like, I don't think I'll ever be found.

936
01:10:42,320 --> 01:10:44,680
So I broke in.

937
01:10:46,320 --> 01:10:48,600
"I have this feeling."

938
01:10:49,320 --> 01:10:53,680
"I think… we… might…

939
01:10:54,920 --> 01:10:57,560
Be supposed to return to Salt Lake."

940
01:10:59,000 --> 01:11:03,120
"And I know
God wouldn't really speak to me,

941
01:11:03,720 --> 01:11:06,280
but I know if you were to ask him,

942
01:11:06,360 --> 01:11:09,640
he would confirm to you
whether or not that was the right path

943
01:11:09,720 --> 01:11:16,680
"because you truly are his servant
and you truly are his prophet."

944
01:11:19,000 --> 01:11:22,280
And he just turned to me
and was like, "Oh, well…"

945
01:11:23,160 --> 01:11:26,280
"God is finally
starting to work with you."

946
01:11:26,360 --> 01:11:29,800
"Now that you recognize
your own nothingness"

947
01:11:30,760 --> 01:11:33,680
"we are supposed to return to Salt Lake."

948
01:11:37,400 --> 01:11:41,280
<i>If you can help us find
Brian David Mitchell for questioning,</i>

949
01:11:41,360 --> 01:11:45,720
<i>please call us now at 1-800-CRIME-TV.</i>

950
01:11:48,720 --> 01:11:53,680
We got off the bus in Sandy,
which is south of Salt Lake.

951
01:11:55,120 --> 01:11:56,520
I was in disguise,

952
01:11:57,160 --> 01:12:01,160
and Emmanuel said he was
taking me back up into the mountains.

953
01:12:02,120 --> 01:12:06,400
I wasn't gonna be allowed
to come, uh, back down again.

954
01:12:08,880 --> 01:12:09,760
<i>911.</i>

955
01:12:09,840 --> 01:12:14,040
<i>Who do I call if I think I see
that Emmanuel they're looking for?</i>

956
01:12:18,280 --> 01:12:22,080
2003, I was a patrol sergeant
for the Sandy City Police Department.

957
01:12:23,280 --> 01:12:26,680
I hear a dispatcher broadcast
that someone has called in

958
01:12:26,760 --> 01:12:29,280
on a possible sighting of Elizabeth Smart

959
01:12:29,360 --> 01:12:31,480
with three people
walking down State Street.

960
01:12:33,480 --> 01:12:35,000
Course, we got numerous calls,

961
01:12:35,080 --> 01:12:37,776
you know, throughout the months,
and they all turned out to be false.

962
01:12:37,800 --> 01:12:43,280
So to be honest, I was very, um,
hesitant to believe it's gonna be true.

963
01:12:45,000 --> 01:12:47,200
We started walking up the sidewalk.

964
01:12:49,640 --> 01:12:52,080
A police car pulled up
and stopped next to us.

965
01:12:52,160 --> 01:12:54,480
And then there were more police cars
that showed up.

966
01:12:56,760 --> 01:13:00,040
And officers started
questioning my captors.

967
01:13:00,920 --> 01:13:03,360
All three parties say
they had no identification whatsoever.

968
01:13:05,120 --> 01:13:06,720
They're messengers from God.

969
01:13:08,560 --> 01:13:12,920
The girl, she was definitely in disguise.
She had a horrible wig on.

970
01:13:13,920 --> 01:13:17,440
Her answers are not making sense.
You can tell that she's very nervous.

971
01:13:17,960 --> 01:13:20,680
So we bring the younger female
over to this location,

972
01:13:20,760 --> 01:13:24,240
separating everybody
probably ten yards away from each other.

973
01:13:25,640 --> 01:13:29,080
This officer,
he was so persistent in his questioning.

974
01:13:29,680 --> 01:13:32,200
"There's this girl.
She's been missing now for a long time."

975
01:13:32,280 --> 01:13:34,960
"The family's never given up hope.
Like, don't you wanna go home?"

976
01:13:35,040 --> 01:13:36,800
And of… of course I wanted to.

977
01:13:38,400 --> 01:13:41,720
But my captors were just right there.

978
01:13:41,800 --> 01:13:43,080
I was terrified.

979
01:13:44,760 --> 01:13:48,600
I needed the safest answer
I could possibly give.

980
01:13:49,360 --> 01:13:52,360
And I says,
"Just for the sake of this nation,

981
01:13:52,440 --> 01:13:56,080
and for your family,
just tell me you're Elizabeth."

982
01:13:57,840 --> 01:14:00,200
And she looked at me and said,
"Thou sayeth."

983
01:14:00,280 --> 01:14:02,160
And I've never heard those words
in my life.

984
01:14:03,160 --> 01:14:05,080
But I says, "I'll take that as a yes."

985
01:14:06,680 --> 01:14:09,720
Then we put her
in the back of Officer Jones' police car.

986
01:14:13,880 --> 01:14:15,800
At that time, she started to cry.

987
01:14:26,800 --> 01:14:30,280
I had a call,
"Come out as soon as possible."

988
01:14:30,360 --> 01:14:32,120
"Don't stop, don't do anything."

989
01:14:33,200 --> 01:14:35,080
"Just get yourself out here."

990
01:14:39,080 --> 01:14:40,960
And I finally got up there.

991
01:14:41,520 --> 01:14:43,440
I walked through this door,

992
01:14:44,200 --> 01:14:48,320
and there is this row of officers
at attention.

993
01:14:48,400 --> 01:14:52,080
And as I'm going past them,
they're all saying,

994
01:14:52,160 --> 01:14:55,800
"God bless you, Mr. Smart.
We hope everything works out,"

995
01:14:55,880 --> 01:14:57,920
and all of these comments.

996
01:14:58,000 --> 01:15:02,080
So I get to the end and I turn the corner,
and there is Cordon Parks.

997
01:15:03,160 --> 01:15:06,400
And Cordon said to me, "Ed,

998
01:15:07,440 --> 01:15:10,080
we really think
that we have found Elizabeth."

999
01:15:16,800 --> 01:15:18,280
I am just going

1000
01:15:20,000 --> 01:15:21,400
crazy inside.

1001
01:15:22,880 --> 01:15:25,520
And we open this yellow door,

1002
01:15:29,400 --> 01:15:32,280
and there is this young woman on the sofa.

1003
01:15:34,480 --> 01:15:41,200
It is not the young woman
that left me nine months ago.

1004
01:15:41,960 --> 01:15:43,960
She was a… a young girl,

1005
01:15:44,040 --> 01:15:47,640
and yet in front of me
was this young woman.

1006
01:15:47,720 --> 01:15:52,520
Her face was sunburned, it was swollen,

1007
01:15:52,600 --> 01:15:55,120
her hair was pulled back in these braids.

1008
01:15:56,880 --> 01:15:59,760
My brain is just going 100 miles an hour.

1009
01:15:59,840 --> 01:16:04,400
And I said, "Elizabeth, is it really you?"

1010
01:16:07,960 --> 01:16:10,280
And then she goes, "Yes, Dad."

1011
01:16:14,360 --> 01:16:18,760
And I held my miracle in my arms.

1012
01:16:22,920 --> 01:16:24,560
It took me a minute to respond

1013
01:16:24,640 --> 01:16:26,960
because, I mean,
I thought I was in trouble.

1014
01:16:29,040 --> 01:16:34,520
But finally, my dad was there,
and he was gonna protect me.

1015
01:16:34,600 --> 01:16:38,320
And no matter what happened,
he wasn't going to abandon me.

1016
01:16:38,400 --> 01:16:40,480
And it was gonna be okay.

1017
01:16:46,840 --> 01:16:49,640
I remember being pulled out of school.

1018
01:16:49,720 --> 01:16:53,800
My oldest brother, Charles,
he said that they might have found her.

1019
01:16:55,000 --> 01:17:00,200
There was just this feeling
of excitement, of… of happiness.

1020
01:17:02,080 --> 01:17:05,640
Just awe in the moment
that she was actually here.

1021
01:17:06,800 --> 01:17:11,560
I remember being so excited
to see my sister and my brothers.

1022
01:17:12,240 --> 01:17:14,720
My mom, she just, like,
was cupping my face,

1023
01:17:14,800 --> 01:17:16,680
and we were all crying.

1024
01:17:26,720 --> 01:17:28,800
I wanted to scream out loud.

1025
01:17:30,800 --> 01:17:34,680
I can't tell you how grateful I was
at that time

1026
01:17:34,760 --> 01:17:37,440
to hear that she'd been found.

1027
01:17:40,000 --> 01:17:41,000
It's over.

1028
01:17:45,280 --> 01:17:46,920
Seeing my family again…

1029
01:17:51,040 --> 01:17:54,800
It reminded me
that everything that had happened,

1030
01:17:54,880 --> 01:17:59,000
it didn't take away from my value
or my worth. Like…

1031
01:18:01,080 --> 01:18:04,880
Those monsters could never take that away.

1032
01:18:11,920 --> 01:18:15,960
Utah's miracle. Elizabeth Smart
is alive and well after nine months.

1033
01:18:16,040 --> 01:18:19,200
Fifteen-year-old Elizabeth Smart
was found alive today.

1034
01:18:19,280 --> 01:18:21,200
280 days after she was kidnapped.

1035
01:18:21,280 --> 01:18:23,160
<i>As if she came back from the dead.</i>

1036
01:18:23,240 --> 01:18:24,920
<i>A story that defies all odds.</i>

1037
01:18:25,000 --> 01:18:27,640
A lot of people all across the country
bursting into tears.

1038
01:18:27,720 --> 01:18:30,000
Spirits are soaring
here in Salt Lake City.

1039
01:18:30,600 --> 01:18:32,360
It's real.

1040
01:18:32,440 --> 01:18:33,440
It's real.

1041
01:18:36,360 --> 01:18:38,080
Everybody's helped. Everybody's prayed.

1042
01:18:38,160 --> 01:18:42,120
We thank God for all the searchers,
for all the people.

1043
01:18:42,200 --> 01:18:43,440
In the history of the world,

1044
01:18:43,520 --> 01:18:46,680
I don't think a little girl has been
prayed for more than Elizabeth Smart.

1045
01:18:46,760 --> 01:18:48,840
And we thank you
for answering those prayers.

1046
01:18:48,920 --> 01:18:50,440
Thank you.

1047
01:18:50,520 --> 01:18:52,920
Mary Katherine is our hero.

1048
01:19:00,480 --> 01:19:03,240
I just remember
being so excited to be home.

1049
01:19:04,640 --> 01:19:06,920
I woke up a few times during that night,

1050
01:19:07,000 --> 01:19:10,280
and both my parents were,
uh, standing above me,

1051
01:19:10,360 --> 01:19:12,040
making sure I was still there.

1052
01:19:17,280 --> 01:19:18,280
My phone rang.

1053
01:19:18,360 --> 01:19:21,760
One of the detectives said,
"Cory, they found her."

1054
01:19:22,600 --> 01:19:27,280
This sense of relief was just unreal.

1055
01:19:28,840 --> 01:19:34,200
I caught a ride with the CBS News crew
up to the camp.

1056
01:19:40,040 --> 01:19:43,560
I stood at the edge, and I was just

1057
01:19:44,680 --> 01:19:45,680
sick.

1058
01:19:51,080 --> 01:19:53,000
And I felt

1059
01:19:54,360 --> 01:19:57,520
like we'd let her down
by not finding her sooner

1060
01:19:57,600 --> 01:20:00,120
and saving her from much of that pain.

1061
01:20:01,320 --> 01:20:05,680
As law enforcement, we have to recognize
that we don't have all the answers,

1062
01:20:05,760 --> 01:20:08,320
and we can't pretend that we do.

1063
01:20:09,360 --> 01:20:12,640
Thank goodness her family
went contrary to recommendations

1064
01:20:12,720 --> 01:20:17,040
from the police department
in terms of releasing a… a sketch.

1065
01:20:23,160 --> 01:20:26,720
This is a case that involved
the strangest people I've ever met.

1066
01:20:30,120 --> 01:20:32,120
I've never lied about anything.
All I've told you...

1067
01:20:32,160 --> 01:20:35,000
Then you tell me the truth.
How did Elizabeth wind up with you?

1068
01:20:35,080 --> 01:20:36,360
Tell me the truth, right now.

1069
01:20:36,440 --> 01:20:39,000
By the power of God,
she was delivered to us.

1070
01:20:39,080 --> 01:20:40,960
Every time we got close to him

1071
01:20:41,040 --> 01:20:44,320
making an actual admission
of criminal conduct,

1072
01:20:44,400 --> 01:20:47,040
he would launch into a spiel.

1073
01:20:47,120 --> 01:20:48,960
- I am the servant of the Lord.
- No.

1074
01:20:49,040 --> 01:20:51,616
And I've only done… I've only done
what I've been commanded to do.

1075
01:20:51,640 --> 01:20:53,160
I found him very crafty.

1076
01:20:53,240 --> 01:20:55,200
Get thee behind me, Satan!

1077
01:20:56,240 --> 01:20:58,440
Get thee behind me, Satan!

1078
01:20:58,520 --> 01:21:01,200
I'm not Satan,
and I'm right here. I'm Cordon Parks.

1079
01:21:01,280 --> 01:21:03,240
Get thee behind me, Satan!

1080
01:21:03,320 --> 01:21:05,200
And I want a rational explanation...

1081
01:21:05,280 --> 01:21:07,480
Get thee behind me, Satan!

1082
01:21:08,320 --> 01:21:11,200
Brian David Mitchell
is a terrible pedophile

1083
01:21:11,800 --> 01:21:15,720
who justifies himself through God,

1084
01:21:15,800 --> 01:21:18,040
and he's capable of anything.

1085
01:21:19,000 --> 01:21:21,080
I don't think he was mentally ill at all.

1086
01:21:21,600 --> 01:21:25,120
But I think he was playing for
a mental health issue, and it worked.

1087
01:21:26,760 --> 01:21:30,120
The district court judge delayed the trial
and delayed the trial.

1088
01:21:34,640 --> 01:21:37,240
The whole case was very frustrating.

1089
01:21:38,880 --> 01:21:42,600
But it… it did give Elizabeth time.

1090
01:21:44,240 --> 01:21:46,200
Time to heal.

1091
01:21:51,320 --> 01:21:53,200
- Hello.
- Hi.

1092
01:21:58,600 --> 01:22:01,840
My family was, of course, very concerned

1093
01:22:01,920 --> 01:22:05,680
about trying to help me move forward

1094
01:22:05,760 --> 01:22:09,160
and to pick up the pieces of my life.

1095
01:22:11,520 --> 01:22:14,440
But when I came back, I was scared of men.

1096
01:22:14,520 --> 01:22:17,520
I was scared of a lot of things,

1097
01:22:17,600 --> 01:22:21,640
and I still didn't hear anyone
speak about,

1098
01:22:21,720 --> 01:22:23,800
like, being raped or being abused.

1099
01:22:23,880 --> 01:22:26,920
I mean, it just…
it was not a common conversation,

1100
01:22:27,000 --> 01:22:30,920
so I felt a lot of shame and embarrassment
around what had happened,

1101
01:22:31,000 --> 01:22:32,960
even though I knew it wasn't my fault.

1102
01:22:33,960 --> 01:22:37,176
It was easy to think, "I should've ran,
should've done that, should've done this."

1103
01:22:37,200 --> 01:22:41,200
You know, it's… it's really a shame that
we don't have both of your harps here.

1104
01:22:42,520 --> 01:22:43,520
Oh, well.

1105
01:22:43,560 --> 01:22:45,520
How often do we get together, you know?

1106
01:22:45,600 --> 01:22:47,560
Would you like me to play the folk harp?

1107
01:22:47,640 --> 01:22:50,920
I think it's your turn
to play the folk harp. I always get that.

1108
01:22:51,000 --> 01:22:53,840
- Is that fish and chips?
- Yeah, that's fish and chips too.

1109
01:22:53,920 --> 01:22:57,360
When Elizabeth came home,
it was a joyous time,

1110
01:22:57,440 --> 01:23:03,280
but it was also difficult
trying to get back to a normal state.

1111
01:23:03,360 --> 01:23:05,080
But what is a normal state?

1112
01:23:05,920 --> 01:23:08,960
Certainly we did a lot of things together.

1113
01:23:12,720 --> 01:23:17,120
My mom, she played a huge part
in helping me process what happened.

1114
01:23:18,760 --> 01:23:21,960
But now, she's ready
to leave it in the past.

1115
01:23:23,480 --> 01:23:25,040
Another Christmas,

1116
01:23:25,120 --> 01:23:28,000
when I got a whole bunch
of really nice stuffed animals,

1117
01:23:28,080 --> 01:23:30,360
and then you threw them all in a bag.

1118
01:23:30,440 --> 01:23:33,520
Yeah, but if you rewind that a little bit,

1119
01:23:33,600 --> 01:23:37,000
Mom said I couldn't do anything
until our room was clean.

1120
01:23:37,080 --> 01:23:38,840
You left me no choice.

1121
01:23:40,240 --> 01:23:43,480
I feel like the things
that really helped the most

1122
01:23:43,560 --> 01:23:46,640
were spending time with my family.

1123
01:23:50,200 --> 01:23:54,400
But the case just drug on
for years and years.

1124
01:23:57,840 --> 01:24:00,560
It felt like the system
was rigged against me.

1125
01:24:02,000 --> 01:24:06,040
And I thought, this has gone on
for almost a decade. It needs to end.

1126
01:24:07,560 --> 01:24:09,080
I don't care what it takes.

1127
01:24:09,160 --> 01:24:11,160
I don't care
if I have to sit in the courtroom

1128
01:24:11,240 --> 01:24:12,640
every day for months on end.

1129
01:24:12,720 --> 01:24:15,600
If this is gonna bring it to a close,
then that's what I'm going to do.

1130
01:24:17,360 --> 01:24:21,200
<i>Elizabeth Smart herself
gave a brave and graphic testimony</i>

1131
01:24:21,280 --> 01:24:22,920
<i>about her horrific ordeal.</i>

1132
01:24:26,960 --> 01:24:29,880
I didn't want to face him.

1133
01:24:29,960 --> 01:24:32,360
But at the same time, if he was released,

1134
01:24:32,440 --> 01:24:34,920
he would definitely
go after another young girl.

1135
01:24:36,480 --> 01:24:39,920
So when the verdict finally came in,

1136
01:24:40,000 --> 01:24:41,960
um, as guilty,

1137
01:24:42,040 --> 01:24:43,280
I mean, it was…

1138
01:24:43,360 --> 01:24:47,200
It was just like,
"It is about time. Thank goodness."

1139
01:24:48,040 --> 01:24:51,520
"It's done,
and I can leave it in the past now."

1140
01:24:53,320 --> 01:24:56,800
I'm so thrilled to stand
before the people of America today

1141
01:24:56,880 --> 01:24:58,520
and give hope to other victims.

1142
01:24:58,600 --> 01:25:00,760
We can speak out, and we will be heard.

1143
01:25:28,360 --> 01:25:31,360
I used to sit and wonder
what my life would be like

1144
01:25:31,440 --> 01:25:33,000
had I not been kidnapped.

1145
01:25:35,280 --> 01:25:38,480
I mean, I had always dreamed of
finding someone who loved me,

1146
01:25:38,560 --> 01:25:40,280
finding someone who I loved.

1147
01:25:42,000 --> 01:25:43,000
And,

1148
01:25:43,720 --> 01:25:47,000
I mean, that did come true.
Like, I-I did find someone.

1149
01:25:48,600 --> 01:25:51,920
And we did get married,
and we do have a family together.

1150
01:25:57,040 --> 01:26:01,800
As time passed, I began speaking publicly
about what happened.

1151
01:26:04,440 --> 01:26:07,520
I just felt like
it needs to serve a purpose.

1152
01:26:07,600 --> 01:26:10,520
It needs to…
to bring some good in the world.

1153
01:26:11,120 --> 01:26:13,160
But we all have a choice to make.

1154
01:26:13,240 --> 01:26:17,360
We have the choice to stay in bed
and keep the covers pulled over us,

1155
01:26:17,440 --> 01:26:19,560
or we have a choice to move forward.

1156
01:26:23,800 --> 01:26:26,880
I can talk about the things that hurt me

1157
01:26:26,960 --> 01:26:30,720
and things that have been
difficult to overcome.

1158
01:26:31,440 --> 01:26:35,080
I wanted survivors to know
that they had nothing to be ashamed of.

1159
01:26:35,160 --> 01:26:37,200
I wanted them to know
they… they weren't alone,

1160
01:26:37,280 --> 01:26:41,080
that there were other people in this world
who have experienced it

1161
01:26:41,160 --> 01:26:42,800
and who can understand.

1162
01:26:45,440 --> 01:26:50,800
As time went on, I began to realize
I'm stronger than I thought I was.

1163
01:26:54,600 --> 01:26:55,840
It took a lot of time.

1164
01:27:01,880 --> 01:27:04,040
I have good days. I have bad days.

1165
01:27:05,760 --> 01:27:10,160
But I've developed
a better relationship with myself.

1166
01:27:11,400 --> 01:27:13,520
My inner voice has changed from,

1167
01:27:13,600 --> 01:27:15,800
"You should've done this,"
or, "You could've done that,"

1168
01:27:16,320 --> 01:27:18,520
to, "You'll make it through this."

1169
01:27:18,600 --> 01:27:20,880
"You can finish this.
You're strong. Keep going."

1170
01:27:25,720 --> 01:27:29,000
You can survive anything
that comes your way.

